Northern shovelers enjoy the weather in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province. Northern shovelers are known for their large spatulate bill. They have a very broad geographical range and are often seen in pairs or small groups of three to five birds. For more photos taken by Lin Ge, check the links below: The beauty of common pheasants Wonderful moment of a little tern capturing fish Beautiful photos of flamingos Feast your eyes on brightly colored orange-bellied leafbirds Beautiful photos of fork-tailed sunbirds Red-headed trogon: A brightly colored bird Beautiful moments of bearded reedlings playing in the snow Hen harrier swoops in to capture its prey (All photos are taken by Lin Ge) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)